It lies between two river mouths - the estuary of the River Tamar ( " TAY-mar " ) to the west ( the estuary is called the
Hamoaze
) and the estuary of the River Plym to the east ( called the
Cattewater
) .

After the restoration , the new king , Charles II , ordered the construction of a massive fort ( the
Royal Citadel
) to protect the town from invaders - such was its strategic importance .
